HOW DO YOU KEEP KIDS IN IT TO

00:42:38.869 --> 00:42:40.869
GET MORE PEOPLE TURNING INTO THE

00:42:42.505 --> 00:42:47.114
INDUSTRY, AS READERS?
&gt;&gt; THAT WAS A GIGANTIC BUSINESS

00:42:51.230 --> 00:42:53.230
QUESTION IN THE 1980s WHEN THE

00:42:55.565 --> 00:42:57.565
COMIC SHOP BECAME THE NEW HOME

00:42:58.860 --> 00:43:00.289
OF THE FIELD WHEN THE NEWS STAND
WAS DRYING UP, BECAUSE PREPARE

00:43:03.592 --> 00:43:06.043
TO THE 1980s, IN AMERICA, IF
YOU WERE A KID, COMICS WERE THE

00:43:06.044 --> 00:43:09.559
FIRST THING YOU BOUGHT OTHER
THAN MAYBE CHEWING GUM.

00:43:16.165 --> 00:43:18.165
AND YOU PROGRESSED FROM READING

00:43:19.234 --> 00:43:21.873
DISNEY OR LOONY TUNES ON UP TO
GETTING THE SUPER HEROES AND

00:43:23.503 --> 00:43:24.734
THEN YOU DISCOVERED THE OPPOSITE
SEX OR SPORTS OR SOMETHING, AND

00:43:29.234 --> 00:43:31.297
YOU GAVE IT UP AND YOU MOVED ON.
THE MODEL CHANGED, AND FOR A FEW

00:43:31.298 --> 00:43:34.167
YEARS THERE WE WERE PETRIFIED
THAT WE'RE NEVER GOING TO HAVE

00:43:34.168 --> 00:43:38.339
NEW KIDS, BECAUSE WE DON'T HAVE
THE NEWSSTANDS TO RECRUIT THEM

00:43:38.340 --> 00:43:40.801
WITH.
TURNED OUT THAT, IN FACT, YOU

00:43:40.802 --> 00:43:45.096
CAN RECRUIT PEOPLE TO START
READING COMICS AT A LATER AGE,

00:43:49.001 --> 00:43:51.001
AND STARTING IN THE LATE '80s
AND VERY HEAVILY THROUGH THE

00:43:53.130 --> 00:43:55.173
'90s, WE BEGAN TO SEE WAVES OF
KIDS COMING INTO THE MEDIUM IN

00:43:55.174 --> 00:43:58.049
HIGH SCHOOL AND IN COLLEGE
YEARS, WITH THE MATERIAL THAT WE

00:43:58.050 --> 00:44:01.970
WERE DOING FOR OLDER PEOPLE.
IN THE LAST 10 YEARS, THERE'S

00:44:01.971 --> 00:44:06.107
BEEN A WONDERFUL RESURGENCE IN
COMICS FOR KIDS.

00:44:07.747 --> 00:44:10.403
THE MOST SUCCESSFUL GRAPHIC
NOVEL OF THE LAST FEW YEARS IS

00:44:14.243 --> 00:44:17.179
THE WORK OF RENA TELGEMEYER,
WHICH CLEARLY REACHES PROBABLY

00:44:17.180 --> 00:44:22.103
AT ITS HEART 8 TO 10-YEAR-OLDS
AND GOES OUT AT PRINT RUNS

00:44:24.780 --> 00:44:26.780
LARGER THAN, SADLY, ANY ISSUE OF
SUPERMAN.

00:44:27.851 --> 00:44:29.298
AND THOSE ARE KIDS WHO ARE
COMING INTO COMICS THROUGH THAT.

00:44:29.299 --> 00:44:31.299
NOT ALL OF THEM WILL BE
INTERESTED IN SUPERMAN

00:44:31.553 --> 00:44:33.553
AFTERWARDS.
BUT SOME OF THEM WILL BE.

00:44:34.601 --> 00:44:36.601
SOME OF THEM WILL MOVE THROUGH
IT.

00:44:36.640 --> 00:44:38.476
AND I'M REALLY COMFORTABLE AT
THIS POINT THAT WE'RE RECRUITING

00:44:38.477 --> 00:44:42.782
A LOT OF NEW PEOPLE OF ALL AGES
TO COME INTO THE COMICS, AND

00:44:44.235 --> 00:44:46.312
THEY'RE JUST COMING IN THROUGH
VERY DIVERSE PATHS, NOT THE SAME

00:44:46.313 --> 00:44:48.574
EXACT PATH THAT MY GENERATION
CAME IN.

00:44:49.798 --> 00:44:52.469
