00:58:29.795 --> 00:58:33.877
THE INDIVIDUAL, SO MANY
PRINTINGS, I REMEMBER VERY

00:58:35.499 --> 00:58:37.499
VIVIDLY, THE GUYS WHO HANDLED
THE NEWS STAND SIDE OF OUR

00:58:38.478 --> 00:58:40.738
BUSINESS, THE MASS MARKET
DISTRIBUTION, COMING IN AND THEY

00:58:40.739 --> 00:58:44.869
WANTED COPIES OF THIS ONE-VOLUME
TRADE PAPERBACK WE WERE DOING.

00:58:44.870 --> 00:58:47.721
WELL, THAT WAS A RETURNABLE
BUSINESS, SO THE MORE COPIES YOU

00:58:47.722 --> 00:58:50.606
PRINTED FOR IT, THE MORE RISK
YOU WERE TAKING.

00:58:52.079 --> 00:58:54.079
AND THE NORMAL PRINT RUN THAT
YOU WOULD DO FOR SENDING

00:58:55.782 --> 00:58:57.899
SOMETHING TO THE NEWSSTAND IN
COMICS AT THAT POINT MIGHT HAVE

00:59:02.202 --> 00:59:04.202
BEEN 50,000 OR 100,000 COPIES,
AT MOST, OF SOMETHING.

00:59:05.099 --> 00:59:07.099
AND USUALLY IT WAS A COMIC BOOK

00:59:08.193 --> 00:59:10.193
THAT WAS A PROBABLY AT THAT TIME

00:59:11.289 --> 00:59:13.289
A DOLLAR COMIC OR A 75-CENT

00:59:14.416 --> 00:59:16.416
COMIC, SO THE COST TO PRINT
WASN'T VERY MUCH.

00:59:17.274 --> 00:59:19.274
IT WASN'T AN ENORMOUS RISK TO
PUT IT OUT THERE.

00:59:20.521 --> 00:59:22.551
WE SAID ALL RIGHT, LOOK AND SEE
HOW MANY YOU THINK WE CAN MOVE

00:59:22.552 --> 00:59:25.602
THROUGH THE NEWSSTANDS.
THEY CAME BACK AND SAID:  OKAY,

00:59:25.603 --> 00:59:29.306
WE NEED 650,000.
AND THIS WAS $3.95 I THINK FOR

00:59:29.307 --> 00:59:31.976
THE FIRST VERSION.
&gt;&gt; $4.95.

00:59:34.220 --> 00:59:35.866
AND RIGHT BEFORE CHRISTMAS TOO,
RIGHT?

